title: Comparative Memeplex Analyzer
description:
Where does your ethical and belief system fall on the memetic spectrum?

A memeplex (religion, ideology, philosophy) is a collection of "memes" -- viral linguistic ideas that repress or otherwise alter our genetically encoded behaviors to maximize their own survival and replication. 

Unlike most political and religious quizzes, this one poses no questions about metaphysical beliefs or abstract concepts. Instead, behaviors and hypothetical dilemmas relating to aggression and reproduction are used as a base-point of comparison against the orthodox positions of major world religions
